<%= render :partial => "settings/sub_menu" -%>

<h2>What are file types?</h2>
<p>
  File types are the core of filtering sources. Each file type has a set of meta information matchers.
  These matchers help parse a filename into useful labelled data. 
  <br/>
  <br/>
  
  For example the Video file matcher matches a filename into information like: 
  <span class="label">Title</span>, 
  <span class="label">Episode</span>, 
  <span class="label">Season</span>, 
  <span class="label">Year</span>, 
  <span class="label">Quality</span> and 
  <span class="label">Edition</span>. These labels can then be used in <%= link_to( "filters", data_file_filters_path) %> to specify what you are looking for.
</p>
<br/>

<table class="data_types_table" cellspacing="0">
  <tr>
    <th>&nbsp;</th>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Extension</th>
  </tr>

<% @data_types.each do |data_type| %>
  <tr class="<%= cycle('even','odd') %>">
    <td width="20" style="text-align: center"><%= !data_type.ignore ? image_tag("online.png") : image_tag("offline.png") %></td>
    <td><%=h data_type.name %></td>
    <td class="variable"><%=h data_type.extension %></td>
    <td width="80" style="text-align:right;"><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_data_type_path(data_type) %></td>
    <td width="80" style="text-align:right; padding-right: 10px;"><%= link_to 'Remove', data_type, :confirm => 'Are you sure?', :method => :delete, :class => 'remove_link' %></td>
  </tr>
<% end %>
</table>

<br />

<p style="text-align: right;">
  <div class="button right"><%= link_to 'Add a new file type', new_data_type_path %></div><br/>
</p>